--> lattice point on a line segment = gcd(abs(dx),abs(dy))+1;
--> pick theorem: S = I + B / 2 - 1 . S=area of polygoan, I=point strictly
inside polygon and B=point on boundary. (take floor of area)
--> regular polygon: exterior angle = 360/n, intrior angle = 180-ext ang.
apothem(distance from side to center) = side/(2*tan(pi/n)).
radius(distance from corner to center) = side/(2*sin(pi/n)).
